text:
Amidst the billions we are alone, from the first breath till our last. 
The boundaries of our souls are etched, upon memories of those we hold dear. 
In the end we are alone, just as we were in birth, this time returning to the ether. 

The journey of life, no matter the zeitgeists and social constructs of the times, shape who we are.  
Human thought, chiseled into the inanimate, echoes through the generations enriching humanity. 
From the first human till the last; we breath the same air; drink the same water; dream the same things. 

As one stands in a golden field, atop a mountain, on the beach; gazing into the endless stars. 
We truly are alone, from the first moment till the last. 
The beauty of life, remains in its brevity.
author: Verus Historie
